text.section:
Each policy shall contain:
a statement that cash surrender values and paid-up nonforfeiture benefits available under the policy are not less than the minimum values and benefits required by this article;
an explanation how cash surrender values and paid-up nonforfeiture benefits are altered due to paid-up additions credited to the policy or indebtedness to the insurer on the policy;
a statement that the method of calculating cash surrender values and paid-up nonforfeiture benefits has been filed with the Commissioner if a detailed statement of the calculation method is not stated in the policy; and
a statement of the method of calculating the cash surrender value and paid-up nonforfeiture benefit available under the policy on any policy anniversary after the last anniversary for which the cash surrender values and paid-up nonforfeiture benefits are shown consecutively in the policy.
